Description: In part one (1 of 2) this extended-length jazz masterclass, jazz saxophone legend George Coleman (Miles Davis, Herbie Hancock, etc.) shares his vast wisdom and experience with you. George discusses improvisation, transposition, jazz harmony, substitutions, personal music stories and more. If you're looking to get an peek inside the mind of a true jazz legend, this saxophone masterclass is for you. NOTE: There is an optional PDF which includes the embedded notation seen in both videos from this series (keys of C and Bb). It is included in the DISCOUNTED BUNDLE AVAILABLE HERE or it can be purchased separately. 

Topics Covered: Saxophone, improvisation, transposition, turnarounds, ear training, jazz harmony, changes, rhythm, triad pairs, substitutions, life stories, etc.
